<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Palfrey" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Palfrey,</orth> a noble horse: <cit><quote>to get my p. from the mare,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 384" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 384</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ven 384" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 384</bibl> <cit><quote>it is the prince of --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 29</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 29</bibl> <cit><quote>in Cheapside shall my p. go to grass,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 75</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>provide thee two proper --s, to hale thy vengeful waggon swift away,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 50</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>